 facts. A number of complex issues in the law-psychology field are addressed, including forensic mental health decision-making, parricide, competency to stand trial, adolescent identity development, penal punitiveness, and offender rehabilitation. In exploring how the current resolution to these and related controversies fail to promote the dignity or empowerment of persons with mental illness, this book suggests how the law-psychology field can meaningfully contribute to advancing the goals of justice and humanism in psycholegal theory, research, and policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aArena, Michael P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArrigo, Bruce A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArrigo, Bruce A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHelms, Jeffrey L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaruna, Shadd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShon, Phillip C. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVoruz, Véronique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Christopher R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791484739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791484739/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles